# read {package.json} as WorkspaceManifest

Provides the repository URL, package manager, workspace conventions, and
supported Node.js baseline.

# read {packages/transpiler/index.ts} as PublicEntrypoint

Defines the root API exported to package consumers.

# read {packages/transpiler/keywords/index.ts} as KeywordEntrypoint

Defines the supported keyword-registry subpath API.

# lang

JSON (RFC 8259 npm package manifest).

# module transpilerPackageManifest

Public npm manifest for the Node.js ESM `@openhint/transpiler` library. The
manifest must resolve runtime JavaScript and TypeScript declarations
deterministically for NodeNext consumers without relying on deprecated
directory or implicit-index lookup.

# entity PackageMetadata

- name: `"@openhint/transpiler"`
- version: `"0.1.0"` for the first public release
- private: `false`
- type: `"module"`
- description: concise public description of parsing HINT specifications and compiling them into implementation prompts
- license: `"MIT"`
- repository.type: `"git"`
- repository.url: `"git+https://github.com/open-hint/hint.git"`
- repository.directory: `"packages/transpiler"`
- homepage: `"https://github.com/open-hint/hint#readme"`
- bugs.url: `"https://github.com/open-hint/hint/issues"`
- engines.node: `">=22"`
- sideEffects: `false`
- publishConfig.access: `"public"`

# entity PackageExports

Declare only these public entry points:

- `"."`
  - types: `"./index.d.ts"`
  - import: `"./index.js"`
- `"./keywords"`
  - types: `"./keywords/index.d.ts"`
  - import: `"./keywords/index.js"`
- `"./package.json"`: `"./package.json"`

Also declare:

- main: `"./index.js"`
- types: `"./index.d.ts"`
- files: `["*.js", "*.d.ts", "*.d.ts.map", "keywords", "README.md", "LICENSE"]`

Do not expose internal keyword modules as stable subpaths. Consumers use the
root API or `@openhint/transpiler/keywords`.

# entity PackageScripts

Preserve existing quality and release scripts. Add:

- build: `make build-js`
- check: `make lint-js && make test-js && make verify-package-js`
- pack: `make pack-js`

# rule

- Keep all development tools in `devDependencies`; the runtime package has no external dependencies.
- Do not publish source `.ts`, test files, `.hint` specifications, Makefiles, Vite configuration, or TypeScript configuration.
- Do not use wildcard export maps.
- Do not add CommonJS entry points.
- The manifest copied to the staged release directory must be directly publishable without rewriting fields during release.
- `npm publish --access public` must not be blocked by `private`.

# test for manifest

- `npm pack --dry-run` includes `index.js`, `index.d.ts`, keyword runtime/declaration files, README, LICENSE, and package.json.
- The tarball excludes TypeScript source, tests, build configuration, and HINT specifications.
- Node ESM resolves `@openhint/transpiler`.
- Node ESM resolves `@openhint/transpiler/keywords`.
- TypeScript NodeNext resolves runtime exports and exported types without TS2834 or TS2835 diagnostics.
